The paper deals with approximation algorithms for clustering problems in metric spaces, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The paper's focus on doubling dimension and the use of approximation schemes suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) categories. The paper's use of approximation algorithms and analysis of their complexity suggests that it also belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining) categories. Finally, the paper's use of information theory in the analysis of the algorithms suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category.
